Now, with as much information as we have put together, I'd like to formulate a fundamental structure of the central progression of the main story. To put it in Fallout New Vegas terms, > getting shot (i.e., why the player should care about what happens) > starting in Goodsprings, talking to Sunny Smiles and asking her about the best route to get to Vegas > fighting the Powder Gangers (or, hell, siding with the Powder Gangers against Goodsprings) > reaching Primm and helping bring Law (or not), and getting directions to the Mojave Outpost > reaching the Mojave Outpost and getting asked to check out Nipton > reaching Nipton and finding the Legion > swinging around through Wolfhand Ranch and headed up to Novac > reaching Novac and taking care of the ghouls at Repconn Test Center > going to Boulder City and resolving the dispute between the Great Khans and the NCR > arriving at Vegas and confronting Benny > choosing a side > committing to a side > fighting the 2nd Battle of Hoover Dam and so this progression actually takes the player through essentially almost every area of the map while progressing the main story on their way towards resolving the main conflict. Please see if you can come up with some suggestions as to various "main story paths". They don't need to be similar to Fallout New Vegas's line of progress (i.e., addressing "not-Primm", reaching "not-Novac", going to "not-Boulder-City" and resolving matters with the "not-Khans", etc etc etc and so on and so forth), it doesn't have to be like that (in fact I'd prefer it wasn't). Just, some sort of progression-of-events that takes the player through a fairly decent number of the districts, has them meeting a pretty good number of factions, etc and so on. See if you can come up with multiple possible suggestions for a main storyline}
