\par \pard\plain \s0\rtlch\af9\afs24\alang1081 \ltrch\lang1033\langfe2052\hich\af3\loch\widctlpar\hyphpar0\aspalpha\ltrpar\cf0\f3\fs24\lang1033\kerning1\dbch\af10\langfe2052\fi0\li0\lin0\ri0\rin0\ltrpar{\hich\af4\loch\cf1\f4\loch
I actually really like 1 through 4. See if there are any ways to combine all four of them. While doing so, some important things to keep in mind:> the initial task should be something simple, yet meaningful. The equivalent to this in Fallout: New Vegas is Doc Mitchell telling you that "you should go talk to Sunny Smiles in the saloon", with the reason being that "she can help you fend for yourself in the desert". This is not to say that Calethina should tell you to "talk to not-Sunny-Smiles" in the "not-Saloon" to "learn how to survive in Antarctica". It should be relevant to the in-game story and world, and allow for as much player freedom as possible. Just that your initial task should be something simple, yet still meaningful, that propels you along the path through the game > at any point in time, the player can always simply think, "Fuck you, not my problem." and be on their jolly merry way, as player freedom and player agency is maximally paramount > maybe let's ease off on "suicides". It could perhaps be a small detail in the world, but perhaps let's not have that as part of the main storyline > Suggestion #4 ("Calethina's Path") could feasibly be a sidequest that you learn about while going about the "go talk to not-Sunny-Smiles" portion of the early-game hook). That being, it's not necessary, but in doing the sidequest, it would allow the player to learn more about the world}
\par \pard\plain \s0\rtlch\af9\afs24\alang1081 \ltrch\lang1033\langfe2052\hich\af3\loch\widctlpar\hyphpar0\aspalpha\ltrpar\cf0\f3\fs24\lang1033\kerning1\dbch\af10\langfe2052\fi0\li0\lin0\ri0\rin0\ltrpar{\hich\af4\loch\cf1\f4\loch
Understood. Here's a unified main story progression that blends the best elements of Paths 1\u8211\'964 into one cohesive through-line, while respecting all your constraints.Overall Main Story Title: "The Bridge Protocol"Core Idea: You are a newly activated Bridge Unit. Calethina\u8217\'92s goal is to use you to stabilize Concordia during its worst energy crisis in decades. The story is about connection, trade-offs, and whether one robot can hold a fractured city together \u8212\'97 but the player is always free to say \u8220\'93not my problem\u8221\'94 and walk away.}
