Expanded Internal ConflictsCentral Hub (13th District \u8211\'96 Axis Mundi)The Central Hub is the political and symbolic heart of Concordia. Its internal conflicts revolve around governance under extreme pressure.Major Internal Conflicts:}
\par \pard\plain \s18\loch\sl276\slmult1\sb0\sa140{\listtext\pard\plain \rtlch\af5 \ltrch\hich\af5\loch\f5\dbch\af5 \u57352\'3f\tab}\ilvl0\ls76 \fi-283\li0\lin0\tx709\fi-283\li709\lin709\ri0\rin0\sb0\sa0\ltrpar{\hich\af4\loch\cf1\f4\loch
Crisis Response vs Long-Term Vision\line The Hub is forced to make constant emergency decisions to keep the city alive right now. This often means abandoning or delaying important long-term projects (infrastructure upgrades, research, cultural preservation).}
\par \pard\plain \s18\loch\sl276\slmult1\sb0\sa140{\listtext\pard\plain \rtlch\af5 \ltrch\hich\af5\loch\f5\dbch\af5 \u57352\'3f\tab}\ilvl0\ls76 \fi-283\li0\lin0\tx709\fi-283\li709\lin709\ri0\rin0\sb0\sa0\ltrpar{\hich\af4\loch\cf1\f4\loch
Central Control vs District Autonomy\line During the energy crisis, the Hub wants stronger authority to allocate resources fairly. Many districts push back, wanting to manage their own power and supplies.}
\par \pard\plain \s18\loch\sl276\slmult1\sb0\sa140{\listtext\pard\plain \rtlch\af5 \ltrch\hich\af5\loch\f5\dbch\af5 \u57352\'3f\tab}\ilvl0\ls76 \fi-283\li0\lin0\tx709\fi-283\li709\lin709\ri0\rin0\sb0\sa0\ltrpar{\hich\af4\loch\cf1\f4\loch
Transparency vs Stability\line The Hub knows the full extent of the grid\u8217\'92s damage. Revealing everything could cause panic and loss of faith. Hiding information risks losing public trust when the truth eventually comes out.}
\par \pard\plain \s18\loch\sl276\slmult1\sb0\sa140{\listtext\pard\plain \rtlch\af5 \ltrch\hich\af5\loch\f5\dbch\af5 \u57352\'3f\tab}\ilvl0\ls76 \fi-283\li0\lin0\tx709\fi-283\li709\lin709\ri0\rin0\sb0\sa0\ltrpar{\hich\af4\loch\cf1\f4\loch
Symbolic Unity vs Political Reality\line The Hub tries to project an image of Concordia as one united city. In practice, it constantly brokers messy compromises between competing districts, which makes it look weak or indecisive.}
\par \pard\plain \s18\loch\sl276\slmult1\sb0\sa140{\listtext\pard\plain \rtlch\af5 \ltrch\hich\af5\loch\f5\dbch\af5 \u57352\'3f\tab}\ilvl0\ls76 \fi-283\li0\lin0\tx709\fi-283\li709\lin709\ri0\rin0\sb0\sa0\ltrpar{\hich\af4\loch\cf1\f4\loch
Resource Allocation as Moral Theater\line Decisions about who gets heat and power are often shaped by political pressure and optics rather than pure need or efficiency. This creates internal guilt and factionalism within the Hub itself.}
\par \pard\plain \s18\loch\sl276\slmult1\sb0\sa140\fi0\li0\lin0\ri0\rin0\ltrpar{\hich\af4\loch\cf1\f4\loch
Undergrid (Virgo District)Because the Undergrid has so many external dependencies, its internal conflicts are especially rich and complex.Major Internal Conflicts:}
\par \pard\plain \s18\loch\sl276\slmult1\sb0\sa140{\listtext\pard\plain \rtlch\af5 \ltrch\hich\af5\loch\f5\dbch\af5 \u57352\'3f\tab}\ilvl0\ls77 \fi-283\li0\lin0\tx709\fi-283\li709\lin709\ri0\rin0\sb0\sa0\ltrpar{\hich\af4\loch\cf1\f4\loch
Human vs Robot Maintenance Crews\line Human crews tend to prioritize safety, caution, and proper procedure. Robot crews prioritize speed and efficiency. This creates constant friction on repair jobs.}
\par \pard\plain \s18\loch\sl276\slmult1\sb0\sa140{\listtext\pard\plain \rtlch\af5 \ltrch\hich\af5\loch\f5\dbch\af5 \u57352\'3f\tab}\ilvl0\ls77 \fi-283\li0\lin0\tx709\fi-283\li709\lin709\ri0\rin0\sb0\sa0\ltrpar{\hich\af4\loch\cf1\f4\loch
Perfectionism vs "Good Enough"\line The Undergrid\u8217\'92s core identity values doing things properly. The energy crisis constantly forces them to do rushed, temporary fixes that go against their nature, creating deep internal shame and division.}
\par \pard\plain \s18\loch\sl276\slmult1\sb0\sa140{\listtext\pard\plain \rtlch\af5 \ltrch\hich\af5\loch\f5\dbch\af5 \u57352\'3f\tab}\ilvl0\ls77 \fi-283\li0\lin0\tx709\fi-283\li709\lin709\ri0\rin0\sb0\sa0\ltrpar{\hich\af4\loch\cf1\f4\loch
Loyalty to the Surface vs Self-Preservation\line Some Undergrid workers feel a strong duty to keep the entire city running no matter the personal cost. Others are beginning to resent being treated as disposable infrastructure by the surface districts.}
\par \pard\plain \s18\loch\sl276\slmult1\sb0\sa140{\listtext\pard\plain \rtlch\af5 \ltrch\hich\af5\loch\f5\dbch\af5 \u57352\'3f\tab}\ilvl0\ls77 \fi-283\li0\lin0\tx709\fi-283\li709\lin709\ri0\rin0\sb0\sa0\ltrpar{\hich\af4\loch\cf1\f4\loch
Old Pre-War Systems vs Modern Patchwork\line The Undergrid contains ancient, high-quality pre-war infrastructure mixed with rushed post-war repairs. Deciding whether to preserve the old systems or rip them out is a major philosophical divide.}
\par \pard\plain \s18\loch\sl276\slmult1\sb0\sa140{\listtext\pard\plain \rtlch\af5 \ltrch\hich\af5\loch\f5\dbch\af5 \u57352\'3f\tab}\ilvl0\ls77 \fi-283\li0\lin0\tx709\fi-283\li709\lin709\ri0\rin0\sb0\sa0\ltrpar{\hich\af4\loch\cf1\f4\loch
Secrecy vs Transparency\line The Undergrid knows many of the city\u8217\'92s hidden failures and dirty secrets. Some workers believe this knowledge should stay internal for safety. Others believe the surface districts have a right to know the full truth.}
\par \pard\plain \s18\loch\sl276\slmult1\sb0\sa140{\listtext\pard\plain \rtlch\af5 \ltrch\hich\af5\loch\f5\dbch\af5 \u57352\'3f\tab}\ilvl0\ls77 \fi-283\li0\lin0\tx709\fi-283\li709\lin709\ri0\rin0\sb0\sa0\ltrpar{\hich\af4\loch\cf1\f4\loch
Resource Hoarding vs City-Wide Duty\line Some crews want to stockpile parts and materials for their own tunnels and people. Others believe everything should go toward keeping the surface districts alive.}
