In terms of the Act 2 progression, for each step, please see if you can suggest several different possible options as to hooks for what could draw the player to the next step. For example, in Fallout: New Vegas, upon reaching the city of Novac, you ask around for the man who shot you. You get directed to a gentleman named Manny Vargas who was old friends with the two guys who'd been accompanying "the guy in the suit" (i.e., that being, Benny, the man who shot you). Either you can help him by clearing out the ghouls in RepCONN Test Site, or by downloading a note from the terminal entry in Manny's room. Either way, you get directed to the next step of the main story progression, which is to go to Boulder City.for each step of the way in Act 2, see if you can come up with at least 3 (if possible, ideally 5) different possible triggers/hooks for leading the player to the next step, all of which are completely optional, in case the player wants to skip steps and go straight to where they want}
\par \pard\plain \s18\loch\sl276\slmult1\sb0\sa140\fi0\li0\lin0\ri0\rin0\ltrpar{\hich\af4\loch\cf1\f4\loch
Here\u8217\'92s a flexible, player-driven Act 2 structure with multiple optional hooks for each major transition.The goal is to give you many ways the player can be drawn from one district to the next (or skip ahead), while keeping everything tied to the energy crisis, the balanced conflict web, and your world. Hooks can come from NPCs, environmental events, data, factions, rumors, or personal motivations.Act 2 Progression with Optional HooksStarting Point (End of Act 1): After completing (or partially completing) the Junction 12 diagnostic in the Forgeward, the player has the data-core and a clearer picture of the spreading crisis.1. From Forgeward \u8594\'3f Hearthward District (or Havenward)Possible Hooks (choose 1\u8211\'963 that feel natural):}
